knowledge_graph.title: Falafel
knowledge_graph.description: Falafel is a deep-fried ball or patty-shaped fritter of Egyptian origin, featuring in Middle Eastern cuisine, particularly Levantine cuisines, and is made from broad beans, ground chickpeas, or both.

related_questions.question: What is a falafel made of?
related_questions.snippet: Falafel is made by combining chickpeas, herbs, spices and aromatics in a food processor to create a mixture that's formed into patties or balls and then either fried or baked. Frying falafel yields a crispier texture than baking.
related_questions.title: What Is Falafel? - Food Network

related_questions.question: Why is falafel not vegan?
related_questions.snippet: Yes! Falafel is considered vegan by almost any definition as these tasty fried chickpea balls are entirely plant-based. Sometimes, however, falafel is served with non-vegan additions like feta cheese or tzatziki sauce, both of which contain dairy.
related_questions.title: Is Falafel Vegan? Our Guide to Choosing Vegan Falafel - Treehugger

related_questions.question: Is falafel good for you or bad for you?
related_questions.snippet: Falafel has several qualities that may benefit your health in various ways. To start, it's a good source of fiber and plant-based protein, two nutrients that work synergistically to help keep you full for longer throughout the day.
related_questions.title: Is Falafel Healthy? Nutrition, Calories, and Recipe - Healthline

related_questions.question: What are the 2 types of falafel?
related_questions.snippet: There are three types of falafel--Traditional falafel, baked falafel and lemon falafel. “Where the traditional falafel is the basic fried falafel comprising a mix of chickpeas, onions, garlic, herbs and spices, baked falafels are made using fresh herbs in the chickpea mixture,” says Chef Sati from Ophelia.
related_questions.title: Everything you need to know about falafel - Hindustan Times

buttons.subtitle: What Is Falafel Made Of?
buttons.title: Easy Authentic Falafel Recipe: Step-by-Step
buttons.snippet: Falafel is a popular Middle Eastern “fast food” made of a mixture of chickpeas (or fava beans), fresh herbs, and spices that are formed into a small patties or balls. It's thought that falafel originated in Egypt as Coptic Christians looked for a hearty replacement for meat during long seasons of fasting or lent.
snippet_highlighted_words: a mixture of chickpeas (or fava beans), fresh herbs, and spices

buttons.subtitle: Is Falafel Healthy?
buttons.title: Is Falafel Healthy Or Am I Kidding Myself? - Women's Health
buttons.snippet: Falafel's Nutritional Profile Zozos says that the health benefits of falafel are plenty. It tends to be relatively low in cholesterol, low on the glycemic index scale, and high in protein. Also, it's full of complex carbs and fiber, which are good for a healthy gut and regular bowel movements, adds Zozos.
